gov.nih.nlm.meme.common
Class Version

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.common.Version
public class Version
extends Object

The Version class provides package version information for gov.nih.nlm.meme.common package. History

08/15/2005:
Suppressible implementation. CoreData has a default value of "N" for suppressible.
06/17/2005:
Many changes to javadocs. Small changes to MapSet to support editor/viewer.
03/11/2005:
Termgroup is Comparable
01/25/2005:
Concept's getCUIs method reports atom last_assigned_cui values as well as last_release_cui values.
12/30/2004:
Minor documentation changes, no real updates.
12/13/2004:
Many main methods were moved to a test suite freeing up individual classes from doing their own testing. Termgroup supports get/setNotes. LoggedError for meme_errors table. Source supports all sims_info fields. ATUI, AUI, CUI, LUI, ISUI, RUI, SUI, StringIdentifier were changed to have more relaxed restrictions and to have int constructors. Concept updated so that "current MSH main heading" logic does not apply to MSH translation atoms.
09/19/2004:
Major change was an overhaul of the molecular and atomic actions. All were moved to the gov.nih.nlm.meme.action package and the classes in this package were updated ot extend those other action package classes for backwards compatability. Each was deprecated. Many classes underwent minor documentation changes. Source was expanded to include all fields required for MRSAB editing. Language object has get/setISOAbbreviation() methods to fully support adding new languages. New MetaCode and MetaProperty objects to represent code_map and meme_properties tables. Termgroup was expanded to include all fields required for adding new termgroups during a source insertion. ContentView was expanded to include additional fields. Also extended to support SUIs in the list.
ContentView was updated to reflect changes suggested by WTH. Some other javadoc was cleaned up. Fixes to MolecularMergeAction and MolecularSplitAction to restore the constructors were made.
07/20/2004:
MolecularSplitAction and MolecularMoveAction now move non-ENG atoms connected to ENG atoms if they are in the same concept and the ENG atom is moving as part of the split or move action. ContentView updated to report whether or not it is auto-generated using a query.
07/09/2004:
Several of the actions have been updated to fully accomodate our testing suites. These include: MolecularChangeAtomAction, MolecularMoveAction, MolecularChangeAttributeAction, MolecularSplitAction, MolecularChangeRelationshipAction. The change actions now support a much wider set of functionality. The move action supports moving concept level rels and attributes, and the split action includes a bug fix. New classes: ContentView and ContentViewMember to support the new content view API. Update to Relationship object to track whether or not it represents the "inverse" of what is in the MID.
06/14/2004:
MolecularChangeAtomAction supports changing source, termgroup, code. MolecularChangeAttributeAction supports changing source, attribute name, and attribute level. RxNormWorklistEntry now indicates whether or not the SCD name is the "dummy" name.
04/19/2004:
Bug in Concept fixed (clears relationships when clear is called). MolecularDeleteAtomAction deletes translation atoms when an ENG atom is deleted. MolecularSplitAction and MolecularMoveAction move translation atoms when the ENG atom is moved. Atom now has methods for tracking translation atoms.
03/17/2004:
CoreData updated to now support adding of attributes and relationships so that any core data element can have attributes or relationships attached to it. NativeIdentifier was upgraded to track the actual core data element that it represents.
02/20/2004:
MolecularDeleteRelationshipAction now supports deleting of attributes connected to the relationship. Relationship now supports the attaching of attributes. CUISource, CodeSource and CodeTermgroup now implement the extended NativeIdentifier API (which includes sg_meme_id, sg_meme_data_type).
02/05/2004:
CoreData has better support for NativeIdentifiers. Relationship also has better support for NativeIdentifiers. MapSet supports containsMapTo and containsMapFrom. MolecularAction has a better toString method. NativeIdentifier has extentions to allow it to be treated like a primitive for serialization purposes. CodeSource, CUISource, and CodeTermgroup were all changed to extend NativeIdentifier. The class was generally updated to be more useful.
01/16/2004:
Fixed a MolecularMergeAction bug relating to a hole in perform action *
Fixed a MolecularMergeAction bug relating to a hole in perform action logic when there are multiple demotions and concept level relationships involved. Changed some other actions to more aggressively read source concept (specifically for handling cases where concept status will change).
01/08/2004:
MolecularMergeAction.getConflictingRelationships() now explicitly ignores SFO/LFO rels as they are releasable now. MolecularAction has a new lockRelatedConcepts method used by the action engine in a new locking scheme. Many molecular actions were updated to support the new method. Concept now tracks a read timestamp so we can identify when a client is using stale data.
12/29/2003:
CoreData was conflating "source id" and "src id", this was fixed.
12/19/2003:
ISUI, LUI, and SUI were updated to extend StringIdentifier instead of just Identifier. MapSet and MapObject were updated to reflect the final MRMAP proposal. New classes Locator, ConceptMapping, and Coocurrence were added (as new CoreData types).
12/15/2003:
The mapping architecture was cleaned up a bit to make it work. It will change again with the next release based on the 12/8 MRMAP discussions.
12/04/2003:
MapSet.getIdentifier -> getMapSetIdentifier. MolecularMoveAction applies MoveInhibitors now. MolecularInsertRelationshipAction reads the source concept if a SFO/LFO (only editor inserted source level rel) is inserted. This should stop the Jekyll errors surrounding changing concept status.
12/01/2003:
Mapping, MapObject, and MapSet were more fully fleshed out. Javadoc comments on how to use MolecularInsertRelationshipAction were updated. PasswordAuthentication was given a toString() method to better report error messages.
11/07/2003:
Molecular actions were cleaned up one last time. Now, when reading of concepts needs to happen it does and the documentation matches. Also, initial classes for mapping were installed.
10/31/2003:
Fixed bugs in actions.
10/23/2003:
Fixed MolecularMergeAction.getConflictingRelationships().
10/22/2003:
Fixed the various molecular actions which do not need to read the concept before performing the action.
10/01/2003:
Fixed the RxNormComponentAtom isExpressedByBaseIngredient method to choose longest of two matchiing ingredients. Before it was choosing the shortest. MolecularMergeAction only looks at releasable relationships when computing the set of conflicting rels.
09/05/2003:
MolecularMergeAction now correctly implements the getConflictingRelationships method, returning conflicts among C (or MSH S) level relationships.
08/25/2003:
RxNormComponentAtom had logic that would allow the "base" and "precise" ingredients to get mixed up (if the precise had a shorter name), even if the precise was marked with a "precise_ingredient_of" rel. We fleshed out the logic to allow precise ingredients to be better differentiated from base ingredients.
08/19/2003:
Bug fix to ActionReport. Bug fix to MolecularMoveAction to properly handle P level rels. Bug fix to MolecularMergeAction regarding changing of relationship status more than once. Refined RxNormAtom and RxNormWorklistEntry logic.
08/11/2003:
New ActionReport object, for obtaining data about actions. RxNormAtom minor bug fix to how it tracks drug and form atom. MolecularMergeAction will not allow merging of same concept into itself. ReportStyle supports the LEGACY CODE(S) section of the concept reports.
08/01/2003:
RxNormWorklistEntry was created to facilitate processing of RxNorm content (in gov.nih.nlm.meme.server.RxNormService). RxNormAtom was augmented to track the RxNorm SCDF and SBDF atoms via the getDrugAndFormAtom() method. Some action classes were adapted to better handle a null authority value (which should never happen).
07/16/2003:
ContextPath updated to contain a list of atoms to the root of the context tree.
06/19/2003:
MolecularSplitAction has an additional flag to toggle when semantic types should be copyied during a split.
06/06/2003:
Coocurrence added. Minor fixes to javadocs.
05/21/2003:
ReportsRelationshipRestrictor had a bug preventing status N P level rels from showing up if there were any matching rels (this was discovered during the CSP2003 test insertion). The problem was fixed. MolecularInsertRelationshipAction had incomplete logic allowing self-referential C and P level rels to be inserted into a concept.
05/16/2003:
Concept deals better with CONTEXT attributes. The various actions were updated to ensure that each would unapprove the concept if the change status flag was set. MolecularSplitAction deals better with inserting the split rel.
05/09/2003:
Atom fixes including: better default for meme_string variable (internal), additional fields (source concept id, source descriptor id) and fix for the way formatted contexts are handled. MolecularInsertRelationshipAction now supports full logic (C level rels delete other c level rels, etc.)
04/25/2003:
Javadoc comments were updated for some classes. The MolecularInsertAtomAction, MolecularInsertAttributeAction, and MolecularInsertRelationshipAction were updated to read the source concept into memory before performing the action. This fixes a aproc_change_status bug in Jekyll. MolecularChangeRelationshipAction was similarly updated. Three new classes: ATUI, RUI, and RelationshipGroupRestrictor.
04/09/2003:
Concept and Atom were changed slightly so they do not perform a check when adding rels to see if they are already there. This vastly improves the performance of reading relationships for large concepts, although it required tweaking of the logic that decides when to add rels to concepts/atoms. The fundamental issue is that when concept_id_1=concept_id_2, the relationship should be added to both atom_id_1 and atom_id_2 but only once to the concept. Atom got clearContextRelationships and clearRelationships methods.
04/01/2003:
Source has a getLanguage method. MolecularMergeAction has a getConflictingRelationships method. RxNormComponentAtom no longer requires that the precise ingredient be longer than the base ingredient. MolecularSplitAction no longer attempts to check merge inhibitors.
03/19/2003:
Certain common objects were optimized with respect to their XML representation. Part of this involved adding methods to these classes to convert from a string to the object itself. For example Authority.Default.newAuthority(String). The objects affected are AUI, Authority, Code, CUI, Identifier, ISUI LUI, Rank, StringIdentifier, and SUI. Improved javadoc documentation. Also a few new classes including BatchMolecularTransaction and MacroMolecularAction and their parent interface, BatchAction.
01/13/2003:
Changes to RxNormBrandedAtom to fix a bug where it was duplicating data by re-implementing superclass methods.
11/13/2002:
Changes include addition of AUI as a clas and its inclusion into the Atom API. Other packages contain changes to support this new field. Additionally, there is enhanced support for RxNorm such as RxNormBrandedAtom but these changes will not appear until the next version.
08/28/2002:
The most significant changes here were the addition of Atom subclasses for supporting RxNorm editing, and the development of a number of classes for supporting Checklist and Worklist management. Refinement of other core classes occurred as well.
06/20/2002:
Atomic and Molecular action classes have been created. Initial Worklist and Cluster classes have been written to support the worklist system. AtomFact and MergeFact and associated classes were written to support the merge engine. RxNormAtom and RxNormComponentAtom were created to represent NLM02/SCD and NLM02/SCDC atoms. These classes plus MeshEntryTerm comprise a set of source-specific atom classes that encapsulate functionality specific to those sources. This is the beginnings of a system to support source editing in the MID.
03/26/2002:
ReportStyle was created to support dynamic and flexible styles for concept reports. This class is used both by ReportsClient and bye ReportsGenerator.

SearchParameter was created to support finder functionality.

The actions API was more fully specified, and in particular, the hierarchy of actions was designed, from WorkLog down to AtomicAction.

Semantic Type problem was settled by creating SemanticType and ConceptSemanticType.

11/01/2001:
1st Release.

Author:
MEME Group
